I have wanted a tattoo for many years but couldn't ever decide on a design that I would never want to change.  I finally decided I would wait until we had children and then would get one representing them.  Unfortunately, in May of 2008, we lost our 3rd child.  I found out the Friday before Mother's Day that I had a "missed miscarriage".  I was just about to start my 2nd trimester.

Four months later, we found out I was pregnant again (quite a surprise since I had infertility troubles).  

We are now blessed with 3 living children and one angel baby.  The symbols on my back are for each one of them - clockwise from the top, my oldest, my second child, Mia - the baby we lost, and our youngest.  The zodiac signs are turned so that the "heads" are all in the center - where my heart is.  

I got this tattoo for my 30th birthday.

description._content: via WordPress ift.tt/X77LXg

HOLD FAST - 11.6.'80 Trent'anni. Quel giorno, era mattina presto, ricordo che fuori faceva caldo ma dentro l'ospedale c'era fresco. Subito dopo l'infermiera, che mi preparò per l'operazione, venne l'anestesista per fare una prima puntura di anestetico: il mondo cominciò a "vacillare". Su di una barella due belle infermiere mi portarono giù al piano terra, nella sala operatoria. Ancora semicosciente ricordo, con tenerezza, il bacio affettuoso sulla fronte di una infermiera (un gesto puramente materno) poi subito mi addormentai. Durante l'operazione mi collegarono ad una macchina cuore-polmoni per poter chiudere il foro tra i due ventricoli del cuore. Il nome del mio "Angelo" è Prof. Gaetano Azzolina. Sono trascorsi trent'anni ma dentro me è come se fossero passati trenta secondi. oggi quel ricordo diventa inchiostro. diventa inchiostro sulla pelle. Indelebile. Un amuleto Tieni duro. Thirty years. That day was early morning, I remember it was hot outside but inside the hospital was cool. Soon after the nurse who prepared me for the operation, the anesthesiologist was to make a first bite of anesthetic, the world began to "waver". On a stretcher two beautiful nurses brought me down to the ground floor in the operating room. Still half-conscious memory, with tenderness, affectionate kiss on the forehead of a nurse (a purely maternal gesture) then immediately fell asleep. During the operation I connect to a heart-lung machine to close the hole between the ventricles of the heart. The name of my "Angel" is Professor Gaetano Azzolina. Thirty years have passed but inside me is like thirty seconds had passed. Today that memory becomes ink. becomes ink on skin. Indelible. An amulet Hold Fast.
